tember 1368","1382":"1382","1380":"1380","1501":"1501","1401":"1401","1368":"1368","1345":"1345","1400":"1400","1431":"1431","1375":"1375","1386":"1386","1409":"1409","22 June 1400":"22 juni 1400","26 SEP 1386":"26 september 1386","1406":"1406","22 June 1401":"22 juni 1401","Woodham Walter, Essex, England":"Woodham Walter, Essex, England","Venice, Veneto, Italy":"Venezia, Veneto, Italië","Henham, Essex, England":"Henham, Essex, England","of Henham, Essex, England":"Henham, Essex, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Oronse, Galicia, Spain":"Galicia, Spanje"},"en":{"5 September 1368–16 May 1406":"5 September 1368–16 May 1406","1368–1406":"1368–1406","1380–1409":"1380–1409","1501–Male":"1501–Deceased","1400–1431":"1400–1431","1401–1431":"1401–1431","1345–1386":"1345–1386","1345–1375":"1345–1375","16 May 1406":"16 May 1406","5 September 1368":"5 September 1368","1382":"1382","1380":"1380","1501":"1501","1401":"1401","1368":"1368","1345":"1345","1400":"1400","1431":"1431","1375":"1375","1386":"1386","1409":"1409","22 June 1400":"22 June 1400","26 SEP 1386":"26 September 1386","1406":"1406","22 June 1401":"22 June 1401","Woodham Walter, Essex, England":"Woodham Walter, Essex, England","Venice, Veneto, Italy":"Venice, Veneto, Italy","Henham, Essex, England":"Henham, Essex, England","of Henham, Essex, England":"Henham, Essex, England, United Kingdom","Oronse, Galicia, Spain":"Galicia, Spain","nameMeanings":[{"name":"FitzWalter","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["Norman, English, Irish: relationship name from Anglo-Norman French  <i>fiz</i> ‘son’ (  see  Fitz  ) + the personal name   Walter  , ‘son of  <i>Walter</i>’."],"variants":[{"name":"Fitzwater","meanings":["Irish: altered form of <b>Fitzwalter</b>, a patronymic from Anglo-Norman French <i>fi(t)z</i> ‘son’ (see   Fitz  ) + the personal name   Walter  , meaning ‘son of <i>Walter</i>’.","History: This is the name of a family of Norman origin, descended from Godfrey, Count of Brionne (died <i>c.</i> 1010). Godfrey's grandson, Richard FitzGilbert, accompanied William the Conqueror and was made Lord of Clare. His great-grandson was Robert FitzWalter, one of the barons who guaranteed the Magna Carta in 1215."]},{"name":"Walter","meanings":["English (of Norman origin), German, Dutch, Polish, Swedish, and Danish: from a personal name composed of the ancient Germanic elements <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i>, <i>hari</i> ‘army’. This personal name was introduced into England both in the reign of Edward the Confessor and by the Normans (in the forms <i>Walt(i)er</i>, <i>Waut(i)er</i>). After the Norman Conquest it soon became one of the most popular personal names in Britain. Compare   Walther  .","Germanized or Americanized form of Czech, Slovak, Croatian, and Slovenian <b>Valter</b> and Czech <b>Valtr</b>: from the personal name <i>Valter</i>, <i>Valtr</i>, of ancient Germanic origin (see 1 above)."]},{"name":"Fitz","meanings":["English: from Anglo-Norman French <i>fi(t)z</i> ‘son’ (from Latin <i>filius</i>), used originally to distinguish a son from a father bearing the same personal name and then conventionalized as a hereditary surname, or short for a surname of which <i>fiz</i> ‘son’ was the first element, for example   Fitzhenry   and   Fitzroy  .","Altered form of English   Fitch  .","German: from a vernacular pet form of the personal name <i>Vinzenz</i> (see   Vincent  ) or <i>Vitus</i> (see   Vito  , compare   Veit  ). Compare also   Fietz  ."]}]},{"name":"Walter","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French personal name of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i>, <i>hari</i> ‘army’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to England, superseding the native Old English form, <i>Wealdhere</i>. It was a very popular name in medieval England, normally pronounced ‘Water’."],"variants":[{"name":"Walther","meanings":["from <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i> ‘army’; name of the famous medieval minnesinger  Walther von der Vogelweide  (  <i>c.</i>1170– <i>c.</i>1230 )."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":13,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Walter FitzWalter 4th Baron FitzWalter was born on 5 September 1368, in Henham, Essex, England, his father, Walter Neville, was 23 and his mother, Eleonore Dagworth, was 23. He had at least 3 sons with Baronnes Joan Devereux. He died on 16 May 1406, in Venice, Veneto, Italy, at the age of 37."},"et":{"5 September 1368–16 May 1406":"5. september 1368–16. mai 1406","1368–1406":"1368–1406","1380–1409":"1380–1409","1501–Male":"1501–Surnud","1400–1431":"1400–1431","1401–1431":"1401–1431","1345–1386":"1345–1386","1345–1375":"1345–1375","16 May 1406":"16. mai 1406","5 September 1368":"5. september 1368","1382":"1382","1380":"1380","1501":"1501","1401":"1401","1368":"1368","1345":"1345","1400":"1400","1431":"1431","1375":"1375","1386":"1386","1409":"1409","22 June 1400":"22. juuni 1400","26 SEP 1386":"26. september 1386","1406":"1406","22 June 1401":"22. juuni 1401","Woodham Walter, Essex, England":"Woodham Walter, Essex, England","Venice, Veneto, Italy":"Venezia, Veneto, Itaalia","Henham, Essex, England":"Henham, Essex, England","of Henham, Essex, England":"Henham, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Oronse, Galicia, Spain":"Galicia, Hispaania"},"fi":{"5 September 1368–16 May 1406":"5. syyskuuta 1368–16. toukokuuta 1406","1368–1406":"1368–1406","1380–1409":"1380–14